House Resolution 316
By: Representatives Hitchens of the 161st and Burns of the 159th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 10, 2025, as Effingham County Day at the capitol and saluting the
2 Effingham County Chamber of Commerce; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Effingham County borders on the Savannah River; includes three incorporated
4 municipalities: Rincon, Springfield, and Guyton; has several smaller communities, including
5 Meldrim, Faulkville, Pineora, Stillwell, Egypt, Clyo, Ebenezer, and Shawnee; and is widely
6 recognized for its outstanding quality of life; and
7 WHEREAS, with a shared vision for growth and prosperity, Effingham County has greatly
8 increased collaboration among its municipalities, the County Commission, and key
9 community stakeholders in order to position itself as the future of the Coastal Empire; and
10 WHEREAS, Effingham County has further partnered with local schools, Savannah Technical
11 College, and other educational institutions to enhance workforce development and provide
12 students with opportunities to engage with growing industries; and
13 WHEREAS, entities such as the Effingham County Health System ensure that access to high
14 quality health care remains a cornerstone of the community, and the county's investments in
15 vital infrastructure serve to bolster its growth and resilience; and
