16 WHEREAS, founded in 1986 to support existing businesses and attract new industry, the
17 Effingham County Chamber of Commerce has long worked to ensure the county's economic
18 strength and well-being through its mission of operating as a member-driven organization
19 "focused on business advocacy and sustainable economic growth" in the region; and
20 WHEREAS, for a number of years, the Effingham County Chamber of Commerce, in
21 collaboration the Effingham County Industrial Development Authority, has sponsored
22 Effingham Day at the Georgia State Capitol, providing a platform for engagement with state
23 leaders and legislators; and
24 WHEREAS, through their tireless efforts and steadfast commitment, Speaker Jon Burns,
25 Senator Billy Hickman, and Representative Bill Hitchens have played a vital role in
26 advancing Effingham County's legislative priorities, ensuring its continued economic and
27 infrastructural development; and
28 WHEREAS, Effingham County Day will once again be observed on February 10, 2025,
29 continuing its tradition of strengthening ties between county leadership and the State of
30 Georgia under the leadership of its CEO, Susan Kraut, and Chair, Kim Iler.
31 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
32 the members of this body recognize February 10, 2025, as Effingham County Day at the
33 capitol and extend to the Effingham County Chamber of Commerce their commendation for
34 the chamber's many important contributions to the Effingham County community and the
35 State of Georgia.
36 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
